	dprr:hasNoteText "While in command in Gaul in 40 (MRR 2.383) he styled himself on his coins as Q. SALVIUS IMP. COS. DESIG. (see now Crawford, RRC 1.528-529, no. 523, 40 B.C.). Salvius does not appear as his nomen elsewhere. Shackleton Bailey suggests that he was a Q. Salvidienus Rufus, adopted by a Q. Salvius; although he kept his former name, he was officially Q. Salvius Salvidienus Rufus (Studies 64)." .
